Revision history for Archive-Tar-Stream

0.06    Wed Mar 18 10:18:29 CST 2026
        - Add transparent GNU long filename/linkname (L/K) support
        - Write POSIX ustar magic instead of GNU tar magic
        - Fix CopyBytes: use ceiling division and BLOCKCOUNT cap (128x perf)
        - Respect safe_copy setting in StreamCopy passthrough mode
        - Use %32C* for checksum to avoid theoretical 16-bit overflow
        - Write 2 zero blocks in FinishTar per POSIX spec (was 5)
        - Make verbose an OO attribute (backward-compatible with $VERBOSE)
        - Fix AddLink typeflag to use string '2' consistently
        - Fix WriteHeader POD (was copy-pasted from ReadHeader)
        - Add gtar and bsdtar compatibility tests

0.05    Wed Nov 19 18:18:44 EST 2025
        - Fix a thinko in the zero byte file copying (the test just happened
          to not catch it)

0.04    Wed Nov 19 13:30:14 EST 2025
        - Fix the copying of zero-byte files and links

0.03    Thu Nov 13 10:48:01 EST 2025
        - Copy all the changes from Fastmail to copy data in much
          larger blocks

0.02    Sat Jan  4 14:59:10 EST 2014
        - [rt.cpan.org #91796] added missing typeflag to AddLink

0.01    Thu Oct  6 20:01:32 CEST 2011
        - Packaged up initial ME::TarStream code from FastMail
        - Added basic tests and documentation
